     1	# zmux
     2	
     3	A terminal multiplexer written in [Zig](https://ziglang.org/), feature-compatible with [tmux](https://github.com/tmux/tmux) and extended with GPU-accelerated rendering, image protocol support, and a native tab UI.
     4	
     5	## Status
     6	
     7	> [!IMPORTANT]
     8	> **Work in progress.** The core architecture is implemented (58 source files, ~10,800 LOC). The binary builds, unit tests pass, and the module pipeline is wired end-to-end. GPU shader implementations and integration testing are in progress.
     9	
    10	## Features
    11	
    12	### tmux-compatible
    13	
    14	- Client-server architecture with detach/reattach via Unix domain sockets
    15	- PTY management (openpty, fork/exec)
    16	- Window/pane layout engine with horizontal/vertical splits
    17	- 5 preset layouts: even-horizontal, even-vertical, main-horizontal, main-vertical, tiled
    18	- Custom layout serialization (tmux-compatible checksum format)
    19	- Key binding engine with prefix key (default: `C-b`) and key tables
    20	- tmux-compatible configuration file syntax with startup fallback from `~/.config/zmux/zmux.conf` to legacy `~/.tmux.conf`
    21	- Dozens of built-in tmux-equivalent commands and aliases (`new-session`, `split-window`, `select-pane`, etc.)
    22	- Status bar primitives with tmux-style option storage and basic format string expansion (`#S`, `#W`, `#{pane_current_path}`, etc.)
    23	- Style parsing (`fg=red,bg=blue,bold`)
    24	- Copy mode with vi and emacs key bindings, incremental search, visual selection
    25	- Paste buffer stack
    26	- Hooks system (19 event types: `after-new-session`, `client-attached`, etc.)
    27	- Background job management (`run-shell`, `if-shell`)
    28	- Control mode for programmatic integration
    29	- Options system with scoped inheritance (server -> session -> window -> pane)
    30	
    31	### Beyond tmux
    32	
    33	- **GPU-accelerated rendering** via Metal (macOS) and Vulkan (Linux)
    34	- **Image protocol support**: sixel and kitty graphics protocol decoders
    35	- **Native tab bar UI**
    36	- **Modern event loops**: Grand Central Dispatch on macOS, io_uring on Linux
    37	- **Clipboard integration** via OSC 52
    38	- **Written in Zig**: memory safety, no hidden allocations, comptime, cross-compilation
    39	
    40	## Requirements
    41	
    42	- [Zig](https://ziglang.org/download/) 0.14+ (developed on 0.16.0-dev nightly)
